The paper proposes a novel deep reinforcement learning model for automatic bridge bidding, which involves decision making under partial information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with game theory and decision making, which are topics covered in the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques, which are covered in the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
